The paper deals with the problem of realizing and selecting rules in a probabilistic setting, which is a core problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the model in music analysis and composition, which falls under the sub-categories of sound and music computing (cs.SD) and speech and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical inference and probabilistic modeling, which is relevant to the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
